CatDescriptText: Jasper K. Washington, hearing aid maker, and Joseph Baxter, chemical worker, Hill District, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, July 28, 1962, pg. 15 with question: "When do you think the Pirates will move into first place?"  Mr. Washington's answer reads: "...and I believe they'll stay there and take the pennant this year."  Mr. Baxter's answer reads: "I don't think they will.  They're still too headstrong from when they won the last time."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Jasper K. Washington wearing hat with patterned band, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown; Portrait of Joseph Baxter wearing medallion patterned button down collared shirt, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
